> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usnish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>snish</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/17/01 4:25:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3540.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Gray Jar continuation in Sharvahl</span><hr size=1> I think I saw someone post about this before, but I couldn't find the thread- so here it is again.<br><br>After you turn in the 4 coins from finishing the gray jar 4 times:<br><br>Merchant Ayyad says 'Excellent, Chemikal few of our kind show a true interest in the more refined arts of pottery these days.  It is very good to see the young people taking interest in the old arts.  Here is a Basic Runequill Set. Take the instruments in the set and practice marking runes on the gray jars that you previously brought to me.  To etch the runes, simply cover a gray jar with some Xakra bile and use the Runequill Set to etch the runes on to the jar. Youll want to fire them in a kiln when youre finished.  When those jars become trivial come back and give me those basic tools and we'll see about upgrading them. <br><br>When you give him the Basic Runequill Set:<br><br>Merchant Ayyad says 'You're progressing nicely, Chemikal take this sculpting tool and add it to the set you already have.  This new quill set will be able to make some very nice urns that should help ease the burden of moving all that heavy clay around.  Take a gray jar and use the new set of tools I've given you to etch Xakra blood into runes on the side of the jars.  These should prove to be very useful in your labors in the future.  Once you have mastered those runes, bring back your runequill set to me for another addition.<br><br>When returning the next runequill set:<br><br>Merchant Ayyad says 'You continue to amaze me with your progress, Chemikal. Here is the final pen to add to your set of runequills.  I have just received word that the king has need of your particular talents.  Take this note to Guard Fareed and he will instruct you further.  Also, this runequill set is able to mark a set of runes on the Grey Jars with Sonic Wolf Blood.  This will enchant the jar and make a great container.  I trust your artistic instincts to guide you.  You should also tell me when youre ready for some [additional instructions]. <br><br>You say, 'I am ready for additional instructions'<br><br>Merchant Ayyad says 'Mastered those runes already, Chemikal?  You're learning very fast indeed.  Your next lesson will be in the molding of a new type of item.  You'll need to gather some gray mud from below the city and mix it with some Rockhopper blood to make a block of reddish clay.  Take this block of reddish clay and combine it with a Vah Shir model sketch to create an unfired Vah Shir figurines.  Fire the model in a kiln with a firing sheet to create a Finished Vah Shir figurine.  Finally, use the Runequill Set to etch grimling blood into runes on the figurine.<br><br><br>After giving the note to Fareed:<br><br>Khala Dun Fareed says 'Ah, you've arrived, good.  Ayyad tells me you're a very quick learner and a skilled sculptor.  The king has taken a fondness for a new game that has been very popular with the people of late. This game, called Brehad, requires the use of a set of 10 Runed Vah Shir figurines in order to play. The king's set was recently broken by a rather intrusive rhinobeetle.  The king would be very pleased if you would create another set for him.  Take this Padded Brehad Case and place 10 figurines in it.  Return the completed set to me and I'm sure that the king will reward you nicely.<br><br>-----------<br><br>My problems are many so far...  I can't get them to say anything else, first of all.  Second, I can't figure out how to etch the clay jar with xakra bile (the first practicing part), or etch any other part.  He says to &quot;cover the jar with the bile&quot; then use the runequill set.  I tried all diff combos with a gray jar, an unfinished gray jar, the runequill set, xakra bile/blood, and/or water, in the pottery wheel, a brewbarrel, and also &quot;Ayyad's Clay Bowl&quot; with nothing but DNC's.  I also tried mixing the gray mud with the rockhopper blood (found off greyhoppers) in a ton of diff quantities with nuthin.  Lastly, I believe that the &quot;named runes&quot; found off various grimlings have something to do with the figurines yer supposed to make for the king.  10 slot container, 10 diff named runes... it seems to make sense.<br><br>If anyone has some insight here I'd greatly appreciate it.  I have just about all the supplies needed but can't seem to combine anything successfully (or fail for that matter).<br><br>snish/chemikal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udemorgoth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Demorgoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/01 4:51:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3540.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Rune</span><hr size=1> I got a quest rune off a grimling somethingchanter outside Katta. Will post name when I get home <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uloentine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Loentine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/01 5:28:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3540.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rune</span><hr size=1> The jars once fired, then you put the fired jars back into the kiln and add the quils and the bile(just one).  This will give you a runed clay jar(container, be warned, 6 slots, 4lbs, 0% wieght reduction).  I am assumeing that you do the same with figurines. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzippdawg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zippdawg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/01 8:05:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3540.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> runes</span><hr size=1> These 10 different runes are found in the grimling mines in ten. Mountains<br><br>etched acrylia runes-<br>wer 4p7g<br>lysn 6p6g<br>amm 9p5g<br>moull 1p9g<br>drurn 4g7s<br>numn 3s<br>lomn 8g5s<br>juln 9c<br>dytl 8s<br>gomn 3g<br><br><br>the prices are what they sell for to vendor.  I bet if you looked at some of the vendors in katta ull see lots of them there.  people farm the mines for cash and sell in katta.<br><br><br>good luck <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usnish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>snish</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/01 4:21:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3540.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> doh</span><hr size=1> I can't believe i didn't try the kiln... it was right fookin next to me.  Thanx fer the info.  Tholuxe just went down for a bit, but I'll def try the higher stuffs when it comes back up.  <br><br>I'll see if I can't figure out how to combine the rockhopper blood + gray mud.  I'm sure there were some combos I didn't try before- just wish he would have said what type of container it was.  I should def be able to try etching the gray jars with sonic wolf blood, tho.<br><br>Has anyone seen grimling blood?  I'm wondering if you're supposed to use those named runes as the blood part.  Once I figure out the combo to the clay, I can test it out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usnish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>snish</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/01 6:40:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3540.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: doh</span><hr size=1> Xakra blood runed jar (the second one)-<br><br>6 slot, 4.0 wt, 10% WR<br>NOT trivial at 148 pottery.<br><br>Will try the sonic blood later. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhonourtruestrike.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Honour Truestrike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/20/01 7:39:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3540.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: doh</span><hr size=1> There is gray mud that is a ground spawn in shar vahl, may mean that one rather than the gray mud off the beetles. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ublyghtnihilist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BlyghtNihilist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/20/01 8:42:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3540.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> when does this start?</span><hr size=1> Is this the direct lineage of the Bard quest after the Wolfbane, or do you start this quest elsewhere? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhonourtruestrike.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Honour Truestrike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/21/01 2:16:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3540.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: when does this start?</span><hr size=1> Had to do the very first part (get a seal by making the very first jar) as part of the shammy quests. No idea if every class ends up doing so. I think anyone who is a citizen can walk up and do the quest. Need the acrylia slate is all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usnish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>snish</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/21/01 11:27:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3540.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> for anyone</span><hr size=1> This quest is for anyone who is a citizen- there seems to be different lines of trade skill quests in SV. Ya got this quest for pottery, the quest that starts with young hopper hides for tailoring, the dart (fletching) quest that begins with collecting xakra teeth, and so on...<br><br>I'm just doing it since I'm already a good potter as a bard and have my coolio 2% cloak. Oh, I think I forgot to mention- the xakra blood runed jar was *not* trivial at 148!! I haven't had a chance to try the sonic wolf blood jar since all the blood I find is going to other classes for the sonic bane weap quest...<br><br>One of these days I'll get around to doing that xakra blood jar a TON to level pottery... seems much easier than collecting old world skins to get past 148. However, the sonic blood is pretty rare, so once I trivialize the xakra blood jars, I prob won't bother trying to level with sonic blood. I haven't had a chance yet to work on combining gray mud + rockhopper blood... will prob do that today.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usnish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>snish</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/22/01 10:10:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3540.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> update</span><hr size=1> Well, I just tried over 20 sonic blood etched jars starting at lev 148 pottery... failed every time and got to 153 pottery.  I'm thinkin these jars are trivial 200ish and *hope* they are pretty nice, at least.  BTW- my int/wis is terrible, but way too lazy to do anything about it.<br><br>Still can't figure out how to make the clay with rockhopper blood + gray mud. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usynionghrym.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Synion Ghrym</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/24/01 6:33:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3540.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: update</span><hr size=1> When a grey jar is etched with sonic wolf blood and tools it produces:<br><br>Fine Xakra Runed Jar<br>4.0wt Cap: 6 Slots/LARGE<br>Weight Reduction 35%<br><br>This was NOT trivial at 169 pottery; 2 attempts = failed once, and succeeded once.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3608.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3587.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3540.topic&index=11><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3540.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3540.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3540.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3540.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><